{"title": "Thieving Pet", "content": "The Nose Knows, by E.W. Hildick, illustration by Unada Gliewe\n\nExactly What It Says on the Tin: a pet animal who steals things. Often, but not always, they then stash them away in a Treasure Room (or doghouse). This trope applies when the pet steals with the intent to keep the item\u2014simply engaging in a playful tug-of-war or a chase with the intention of being caught does not count.\n\nThis can lead to Mistaken for Thief if someone is thought to have stolen something that was actually stolen by a pet.\n\nOften seen in Kid Detective stories.\n\nA variant is a pet owned by a thief which has been specifically trained for the task.\n\nCan be Truth in Television.\n\nCompare to Thieving Magpie, which isn't a pet (usually). Compare Pet Gets the Keys and Animal Assassin.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThievingPet", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Clue", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/GothamAcademy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/Aladdin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TitanicTheLegendGoesOn", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/FantasticBeasts", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/FantasticBeastsTheCrimesOfGrindelwald", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheDollPeople", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/MillyMolly", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheBradyBunch", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Community", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/AmericasFunniestHomeVideos", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Pokemon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaMajorasMask", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Nethack", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/PhoenixWrightAceAttorneyJusticeForAll", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MarthaSpeaks", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/HandyManny", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/ScoobyDooMysteryIncorporated"], "non_media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExactlyWhatItSaysOnTheTin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TreasureRoom", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MistakenForThief", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KidDetective",